Source: nemoclaw-firstboot
Section: admin
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Jason Perlow <jperlow@nvidia.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13)
Standards-Version: 4.7.0
Rules-Requires-Root: no

Package: nemoclaw-firstboot
Architecture: all
Depends:
 ${misc:Depends},
 git,
 bash,
 nodejs (>= 22),
 npm,
 adduser,
 ca-certificates,
 patch
Description: nemoclaw first-boot git clone + npm install glue
 Clones https://github.com/NVIDIA/nemoclaw at first boot into
 /var/lib/nemoclaw, runs npm install, applies any runtime patches
 shipped in /etc/nemoclaw/patches/, and enables ff-only git fetch on
 every subsequent boot so the device tracks upstream main HEAD.
 .
 Replaces the separate nemoclaw-core + nemoclaw-firstboot Yocto recipes
 with a single glue package; source is fetched at boot rather than
 embedded in the deb to genuinely track upstream master.
